content.description: Wide crack with some hands in the back, up to a short but clean and fun finger crack crux.  Exit the finger crack and continue up a more broken system to the top.  Belay on gear and walk off.
content.protection: Single rack, a couple extra finger size.
content.location: Just right of the first large left facing corner you come to when heading east along the base.  You should see a clean looking finger crack with a little zig in it about 1/2 way up the wall.

content.description: Mixed bag - some nice hands, some more facey stuff, a thin crack up higher.  Varied climbing mostly in a left facing corner.  Build a gear anchor up top and the walk off.
content.location: Near the west end of the formation, this is the first large-ish left facing and left leaning corner you will see.  Starts up a short slab/broken block into a bush before you can gain the initial crack.

pathTokens: Laramie Peak Wildlife Habitat Management Area
